Enable port forwarding for the Mikrotik router

Click "IP" > "Firewall" > "NAT" > "Add New" 

1 Chain: dstnat
2 Protocol: tcp
3 Dst. Port: 80
4 In. Interface: ether1-gateway (one of an interface on the router)

5 Scroll page down to "Action" field
6 Action : dst-nat
7 To Addresses: 192.168.88.253 (IP address of the computer cFos Personal Net is running on)
8 To Ports: 80

9 Scroll back on top of the page and check if the rule enabled (by default it is Enabled)
10 Click "Apply"
11 Click "OK" and then logoff from the router
